race.description: Lucky's Scrap Metals Boxing Day Cup CG&E Handicap
race.comment: THE LITTLE GENERAL (8) is a progressive three-year-old who broke his maiden in emphatic style last start, leading all the way to coast home over 1300m at Hawkesbury. Should dictate terms again. Plenty of improvement in store so stick with him. COMMANDING ARTIST (3) returned from a 23-week spell with a tough win last time out over 1300m at Hawkesbury in a Class 1. Has had his problems but looks to be back in great shape so it will be no surprise if he goes right on with it. ZOOMORPHIC (6) led by a big space on the bend then dug deep to hold off his BM58 rivals over 1400m at Scone recently. Probably takes the sit today and with 4kgs less than last start he will be difficult to hold out. CALTSAR (2) went to the paddock in winning form and has to be kept safe in his return.
